    3.—(1)  In formulating any relevant proposals, a licence holder or a person authorised by an exemption to generate or supply electricity—(a)  shall have regard to the desirability of preserving natural beauty, of conserving flora, fauna and geological or physiographical features of special interest and of protecting sites, buildings and objects of architectural, historic or archaeological interest; and
